.TH "rc_keydown_notimeout" 9 "rc_keydown_notimeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rc_keydown_notimeout \- generates input event for a key press without an automatic keyup event at a later time
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rc_keydown_notimeout
.BI "(struct rc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "enum rc_proto protocol "  ","
.BI "u64 scancode "  ","
.BI "u8 toggle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the struct rc_dev descriptor of the device
.IP "protocol" 12
the protocol for the keypress
.IP "scancode" 12
the scancode for the keypress
.IP "toggle" 12
the toggle value (protocol dependent, if the protocol doesn't
support toggle values, this should be set to zero)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is used to signal that a key has been pressed on the
remote control. The driver must manually call \fBrc_keyup\fP at a later stage.
